cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the application of computer vision and deep learning techniques for the identification and quantification of biotic stress in coffee leaves. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a popular deep learning technique, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of data augmentation techniques and the exploration of different models suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the estimation of stress severity, which involves the use of regression techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) possible categories as well.
